data.text: I don't think I cooked my dinner right. I'm having an existential crisis.
Pretty sure at this point there's been more versions of Peter Shillito than Google Chrome. I wonder if I'll recognise myself one day.
It's certainly helped with being awkward around people I don't know.
If I was asked if I wanted to go see NXT Wrestling a few years ago, I would've said he'll no. Ditto going to concerts and films on my own.
Like, you're with people you know and like, so worst case scenario you're hanging with friends. Best case scenario you enjoy it.
The film takes it to the extreme, saying no is allowed, but if someone says "hey want to go to [thing you think you don't like]" say yes.
I mean that on a serious level btw. A number of years ago I had therapy and one of the things highlighted was my reluctance to say "yes".
